PRE-PROCESSING OF DATA

# Load the NHIS dataset
nhis_data <- read_csv("/Users/pavan/Downloads/nhis_2022.csv")
## Rows: 35115 Columns: 48
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (3): NHISHID, NHISPID, HHX
## dbl (45): YEAR, SERIAL, STRATA, PSU, REGION, PERNUM, SAMPWEIGHT, ASTATFLG, C...
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Handle special codes (996, 997, 998, 999 -> NA)
missing_codes <- c(996, 997, 998, 999)
nhis_data_cleaned <- nhis_data %>%
  mutate(across(everything(), ~ ifelse(. %in% missing_codes, NA, .)))

# Subset: Adults only (Age >= 18), valid diabetes information
subset_diabetes <- nhis_data_cleaned %>%
  filter(AGE >= 18, DIABETICEV %in% c(1, 2)) %>%
  mutate(DIABETICEV = factor(DIABETICEV, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c("No", "Yes"))) %>%
  drop_na()

# Select predictor variables
features_diabetes <- c('AGE', 'BMICALC', 'HRSLEEP', 'MOD10DMIN', 
                       'FRUTNO', 'VEGENO', 'SODAPNO', 'FRIESPNO', 
                       'PIZZANO', 'SPORDRMNO', 'ALCDAYSYR')

# Prepare modeling dataset
model_data <- subset_diabetes %>%
  select(DIABETICEV, all_of(features_diabetes)) %>%
  drop_na()

cat("Modeling dataset size:", nrow(model_data), "rows\n")
## Modeling dataset size: 20995 rows
# Separate predictors and target
X <- model_data %>% select(-DIABETICEV)
y <- model_data$DIABETICEV

# Standardize features
scaler <- preProcess(X, method = c("center", "scale"))
X_scaled <- predict(scaler, X)

TRAIN-TEST SPLIT

# 70-30 train-test split with stratification
set.seed(19)
train_indices <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)

X_train <- X_scaled[train_indices, ]
X_test <- X_scaled[-train_indices, ]
y_train <- y[train_indices]
y_test <- y[-train_indices]

# Check class balance
cat("Train class balance:\n")
## Train class balance:
print(table(y_train))
## y_train
##    No   Yes 
## 13226  1471
cat("Test class balance:\n")
## Test class balance:
print(table(y_test))
## y_test
##   No  Yes 
## 5668  630

BASIC LINEAR SVM MODEL

# Train a basic Linear SVM
svm_linear_full <- svm(
  x = X_train,
  y = y_train,
  kernel = "linear",
  cost = 1,
  scale = FALSE
)

# Predict
y_pred_linear_full <- predict(svm_linear_full, X_test)

# Evaluate
confusion_linear_full <- table(Predicted = y_pred_linear_full, Actual = y_test)
print(confusion_linear_full)
##          Actual
## Predicted   No  Yes
##       No  5668  630
##       Yes    0    0
accuracy_linear_full <- sum(diag(confusion_linear_full)) / sum(confusion_linear_full)
cat("Accuracy (Linear SVM):", round(accuracy_linear_full, 4), "\n")
## Accuracy (Linear SVM): 0.9

VARIABLE IMPORTANCE PLOT

library(ggplot2)
# Extract feature importance for Linear SVM
coefs <- svm_linear_full$coefs
SVs <- svm_linear_full$SV
weights <- t(coefs) %*% as.matrix(SVs)

importance_df <- data.frame(
  Feature = colnames(X_train),
  Importance = abs(as.vector(weights))
)

importance_df <- importance_df %>% arrange(desc(Importance))
print(importance_df)

# Standardize predictors

X_scaled_reduced <- predict(scaler_reduced, X_reduced)

# Train-Test Split 

set.seed(19)

train_indices_reduced <- createDataPartition(y_reduced, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)

X_train_reduced <- X_scaled_reduced[train_indices_reduced, ]
X_test_reduced <- X_scaled_reduced[-train_indices_reduced, ]
y_train_reduced <- y_reduced[train_indices_reduced]
y_test_reduced <- y_reduced[-train_indices_reduced]

# Confirm new split

# Retrain Linear SVM (with Class Weights) on Reduced Data

svm_linear_reduced <- svm(
  x = X_train_reduced,
  y = y_train_reduced,
  kernel = "linear",
  cost = 1,
  class.weights = c("No" = 1, "Yes" = 5),
  scale = FALSE
)

# Predict and evaluate
y_pred_linear_reduced <- predict(svm_linear_reduced, X_test_reduced)
confusion_linear_reduced <- table(Predicted = y_pred_linear_reduced, Actual = y_test_reduced)

cat("\nConfusion Matrix (Linear SVM - Reduced Features):\n")
## 
## Confusion Matrix (Linear SVM - Reduced Features):

## 
## Test Accuracy (Linear SVM - Reduced Features): 0.7877
# Precision, Recall, F1 Score for Linear SVM (Reduced Features)

TP_lr <- confusion_linear_reduced["Yes", "Yes"]
FP_lr <- confusion_linear_reduced["Yes", "No"]
FN_lr <- confusion_linear_reduced["No", "Yes"]

precision_lr <- TP_lr / (TP_lr + FP_lr)
recall_lr <- TP_lr / (TP_lr + FN_lr)
f1_lr <- 2 * (precision_lr * recall_lr) / (precision_lr + recall_lr)

cat("\nPrecision (Linear Reduced):", round(precision_lr, 4))

PLOTTING LINEAR SVM

# Train mini SVM on two most important features (AGE, BMICALC)
X_train_mini <- X_train_reduced %>% select(AGE, BMICALC)
X_test_mini <- X_test_reduced %>% select(AGE, BMICALC)

svm_linear_mini <- svm(
  x = X_train_mini,
  y = y_train_reduced,
  kernel = "linear",
  cost = 1,
  class.weights = c("No" = 1, "Yes" = 5),
  scale = FALSE
)

# Create grid
grid <- expand.grid(
  AGE = seq(min(X_train_mini$AGE), max(X_train_mini$AGE), length.out = 200),
  BMICALC = seq(min(X_train_mini$BMICALC), max(X_train_mini$BMICALC), length.out = 200)
)

# Predict on grid
grid$pred <- predict(svm_linear_mini, newdata = grid)

# Plot
ggplot(grid, aes(x = AGE, y = BMICALC)) +
  geom_tile(aes(fill = pred), alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_point(data = X_train_mini %>% mutate(label = y_train_reduced),
             aes(color = label), size = 1.5) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("No" = "#cce5ff", "Yes" = "#f8d7da")) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("No" = "#007bff", "Yes" = "#dc3545")) +
  labs(title = "Linear SVM Decision Boundary (AGE vs BMICALC)",
       x = "Standardized AGE", y = "Standardized BMICALC") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14)

# Combine all the important results first

comparison_df <- tibble(

  Accuracy = c(accuracy_linear_reduced, accuracy_radial_reduced, accuracy_poly_reduced),
  Precision = c(precision_lr, precision_radial, precision_poly),
  Recall = c(recall_lr, recall_radial, recall_poly),
  F1_Score = c(f1_lr, f1_radial, f1_poly)
)

# View the table
print(comparison_df)
## # A tibble: 3 × 5
##   Model          Accuracy Precision  Recall F1_Score
##   <chr>             <dbl>     <dbl>   <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1 Linear SVM        0.788     0.252 0.571    0.350  
## 2 Radial SVM        0.797     0.256 0.541    0.347  
## 3 Polynomial SVM    0.862     0.5   0.00317  0.00631

  pivot_longer(cols = -Model, names_to = "Metric", values_to = "Value")

Tuned POLYNOMIAL SVM WITH MINI DATASET

# Sample 500 from each class due to computational issues
set.seed(19)
yes_big <- model_data_diabetes_reduced %>% filter(DIABETICEV == "Yes") %>% slice_sample(n = 500)
no_big  <- model_data_diabetes_reduced %>% filter(DIABETICEV == "No") %>% slice_sample(n = 500)
mini_big_data <- bind_rows(yes_big, no_big)
X_big <- mini_big_data %>% select(-DIABETICEV)
y_big <- mini_big_data$DIABETICEV

scaler_big <- preProcess(X_big, method = c("center", "scale"))
X_scaled_big <- predict(scaler_big, X_big)

set.seed(19)
train_idx_big <- createDataPartition(y_big, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)
X_train_big <- X_scaled_big[train_idx_big, ]
X_test_big  <- X_scaled_big[-train_idx_big, ]
y_train_big <- y_big[train_idx_big]
y_test_big  <- y_big[-train_idx_big]
# Combine for training
train_data_big <- cbind(DIABETICEV = y_train_big, X_train_big)

# Tune polynomial SVM
set.seed(19)
tune_poly_big <- tune.svm(DIABETICEV ~ ., data = train_data_big,
                          kernel = "polynomial",
                          degree = c(2, 3),
                          cost = c(0.1, 1, 10,100),
                          class.weights = c("No" = 1, "Yes" = 1),
                          scale = FALSE)

# Evaluate
best_poly_big <- tune_poly_big$best.model
y_pred_big <- predict(best_poly_big, X_test_big)
conf_mat_big <- confusionMatrix(y_pred_big, y_test_big, positive = "Yes")
print(conf_mat_big)

New comparison

# Load library
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)

# Create model performance data
model_perf <- data.frame(
  Model = c("Linear SVM", "Radial SVM", "Polynomial SVM", "Tuned Poly SVM (Mini 1000)"),
  Accuracy = c(0.7877, 0.7966, 0.8550, 0.6633),
  Precision = c(0.2523, 0.2512, 0.5000, 0.6150),
  Recall = c(0.5714, 0.5063, 0.0032, 0.8733),
  F1_Score = c(0.3500, 0.3358, 0.0063, 0.7230)
)

# Reshape to long format
model_perf_long <- model_perf %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = -Model, names_to = "Metric", values_to = "Score")

# Plot
ggplot(model_perf_long, aes(x = Metric, y = Score, fill = Model)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 0.8)) +
  labs(title = "Model Performance Comparison",
       x = "Metric", y = "Score") +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13)
